Wars bring humanitarian disasters to ordinary people while hugely benefiting the military-industrial complex that often profiteers from military conflicts by selling weapons and panic-mongering. As the world's No. 1 arms exporter, the U.S. is well known for making a big fortune during wars. Credits: Editor: Yuan Xin Designer: Cao Yi Senior producer: Wei Wei Managing director: Mei Yan (To submit cartoons and share story ideas or feedback on our cartoon page, please contact us at cartoon_opinions@cgtn.com)